children.subject: Is that the Entrepreneurship? How was it, and was it more like 3 units or 4? I read on RateMyProf that the prof was arrogant and he had horrible reviews, but I like the subject a lot... so idk
I took a 2 unit class ...UGBA C5, though the work load was a bit high for a 2 unit class. Not sure if it is being offered in the fall. No exams.
Maybe combine a Decal and a PE class, they're pretty fun and good for personal growth, although you'd need to attend the section.
UGBA 135 (personal finance) is 2 units and may be helpful for life in general. There's one 2-hour lecture every week and not much work.

history.content: I need 2 more units to meet the minimum unit requirement for next semester, and was wondering what to take. For reference I'm an EECS major and I've already finished all my H/SS requirements so taking any more H/SSes would be pointless. Ideally the 2 units should be as little work as possible, as I will not have any time to devote to them. Any suggestions other than CS 370 appreciated. Thanks.
